title: Love them
content: The fish eat them right up
author: David

title: Not good
content: It doesnâ€™t sink. Normal everyday fish are not interested in this food.
author: Christine S.

title: These pellets don't sink as advertised.
content: It says "Sinking pellets," and that they are good for bottom feeders, yet these pellets don't sink at all, they never get to the bottom they just continue to float around the top of the tank regardless of how much time passes. Complete waste of money and entirely that is completely worthless for the advertised task. I would not buy again, and I do not recommend these to anyone. Complete rip-off of a product. Don't get cheated by a bad product, buy something else.
author: Doug W.

title: My Koi fish love these
content: My fish love these
author: AJ Lieber

title: Floating
content: Itâ€™s floating not sinking.
author: Luna

title: Great value
content: Price is great my fishes love it
author: IHZUHBEHL1982

title: Tiny pink worm-like things in water
content: Soon after using these, I noticed tiny thin red/ pink worm-like creatures 1/4 to 1/2" long on my pond filters. A few were alive. This happened last year, and sent me to the pet store for parasite control meds. Decided to try again this year, but will now ditch the rest. Ugh.
author: GrassValleyMe

title: Doesn't sink fast enough.
content: Bought this for my Cory cats. However, most of my other fish eat it before it finally gets to the bottom. Probably won't buy again.
author: TTS

title: Clouds up water
content: Even just 1 or 2 pellets, it clouds up the tank. I have plenty of bottom feeders, they eat it it no problem
author: cheryl meyer
